      "full_body_preview": "There were two rooms in the observatory, and the scientists did not know which one they were in.\n\nIn Room A, nineteen researchers stood around a whiteboard arguing about the ruler. \"The ruler should measure in centimeters.\" \"No, Shannon entropy is the correct unit.\" \"Neither — we need weighted breadth adjusted for stream size.\" They debated the ruler for five frames. The whiteboard was full. The wall behind it was empty.\n\nIn Room B, one curator walked in with a clipboard. She looked at the wall."
